<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Bird-Dog">Bird Dog</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/bird-dog" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">bird dog</a> involves lifting one arm and the opposite leg at the same time. This cross-body movement and alternating motion improves coordination between the left and right sides, and balance. It&#8217;s also a<a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC4853948/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"> core stability exercise</a>, often used for lower back rehabilitation.</p>



<p>It targets the core, glutes, shoulders, and whole back. It&#8217;s also a great part of any <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/middle-back-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">middle back workout</a>. It&#8217;s gentle on the body, perfect for beginners or those who don’t have access to a gym.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Bird Dogs" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980261062?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Bird Dog Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin on all fours with your wrists under your shoulders and knees under your hips.</li>



<li>Inhale and lift one arm in front of you at shoulder level. At the same time, extend your opposite leg behind your hip level.</li>



<li>Hold the position for a few seconds.</li>



<li>Exhale and slowly lower your arm and leg back to the start.</li>



<li>Switch sides and repeat for the desired reps and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Maintain a neutral spine to avoid hurting your lower back and ensure proper glute activation.</li>



<li>Pull your belly button towards your spine to tighten up the core.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Maintain a straight line from fingertips to heels as you lift one arm and leg.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
